FBIS4-24399 "drchi104_k_94024" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Guangzhou Holds Photo Exhibit on Deng Xiaoping Guangzhou Holds Photo Exhibit on Deng Xiaoping OW2805141394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1336 GMT 28 May 94 OW2805141394 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Guangzhou, May 28 (XINHUA) -- An exhibition of photographs depicting the historic activities and daily life of Deng Xiaoping opened in Guangzhou on Saturday [28 May]. Xie Fei, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and secretary of Guangdong Provincial Committee of the CPC, took part in the opening ceremony. The exhibition of more than 520 photos record Deng's activities in the period of the new democratic revolution and in the construction of socialist China. Pictures depicting Deng's political activities and daily life since China began to carry out the policy of reform and opening are especially displayed, including his successive inspection tours of Guangdong and his inspection of south China in 1992.
